{
  "stem": "1061.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, they just threw it at you, and if it didn't fit, too bad.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Wooden shoes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And with-- at the time, when the train was unloaded in Auschwitz, we saw Father emerge from the train.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It so happened that our wagon was adjacent to the men's.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You know, the men's-- the men's wagons were a few, and they ended.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then the others started.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Where we went in the first female wagon, and Father was in the last men's wagon.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So when we were unloaded, on the platform in Auschwitz, we still saw Father there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But of course later on, he did not survive.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Very soon, he became very ill because he was-- you see, after Mother-- after Mother was taken away, he changed terribly.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He became totally gray and despondent, and he didn't have that spark in him any more and not a sense of humor.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I think he really lived because we were around.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he-- he might as the situation was horrible for-- for all of us, I think that sustained him.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But once we came to Auschwitz and we were totally separated-- he went with the men somewhere on the men's side.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we went somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We found out from people from my hometown who came with the same transport that he actually disintegrated in a very short time.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So by October, I think, he-- he was-- he died.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And of course-- of course I'm sure he went to crematory.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so we have never seen him again-- never after seeing him on the platform in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Mother went-- Mother perished in Treblinka two years before that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And now Father perished, and now the three of us were left.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Was there a selection when you arrived at Auschwitz?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This is why, as I've told you before, they were very little kids in our camp in Starachowice, and these kids were let through.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were five- and six-year-olds.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because, you see, this was by then-- I understand now from reading and doing research on the subject-- that some of the crematories were gone and, you know, this was now, really, the heat was on the Germans.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But of course, there was still plenty of suffering ahead of us, which we really didn't know.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But-- and we didn't know why we were sent out of Starachowice.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You see, we-- we were in the eye of the storm, but we never knew what was really happening as far as the war was concerned.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We-- we-- we didn't know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean, we didn't have papers.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We didn't-- nobody told us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I mean, we-- we had no idea that there was a Russian offensive from the East and there was going-- there was now a build up on the West-- in the West-- you know, that the Americans and the English were-- were trying to-- to bring an end to the war.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But we know-- we knew nothing of that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We just knew that our suffering has now increased.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the rest of what was the bit of humanity that still remained with us in those-- in those camps in our hometown was now very much over.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I mean, that was now-- it wasn't a surreal world.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "This was hell.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I mean, now this was living hell, and-- and this was something that we couldn't even comprehend.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I mean, we could comprehend being exhausted, and being hungry, and having lice, and working, and all.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "You know, and-- and-- and understanding the war effort, how they would squeeze the blood out of us for their war effort-- we could understand that, even I could.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But this place, Auschwitz, it was something incomprehensible.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I mean, we didn't really know the-- what the purpose of this place was, since we really never knew that this was a real killing camp-- that there were people coming in transport right into the-- into the crematories and into-- out the chimney.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We had no idea.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But this place didn't look like-- it had barbed wire that was electrified.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were taken into a barracks-- again, a lot of us from my hometown, you see?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were still in the group.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were placed in the barracks, and we were on a type of a quarantine for about a month in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And what does quarantine mean?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That means that you were not 'privileged'-- quote, unquote-- 'privileged' to work outside of the camp.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there was nothing to do in the camp, so they had a pile of rocks on one end and a pile of rocks on the other end.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They had one group of women carrying rocks from here to that pile, and then the other group from here to there.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You see?",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
